name: Peter Dutton
summary: Peter Dutton, Australia's opposition leader, has made several controversial statements and policy proposals. He has threatened to block an offshore wind project, vowing to have armed guards at Jewish schools and synagogues after an arson attack, and promised never to stand in front of an Aboriginal flag as prime minister. Additionally, he has proposed a new antisemitism taskforce and changes to the Migration Act to tackle antisemitism. Dutton has also pledged to push for gas power, despite criticism from Labor seats, and has retracted his promise to cut net migration. His recent visit to a Syrian prison camp has also raised concerns about his judgment.
